                            <comment id="14463833" author="rene.de.bloois" created="Wed, 5 Dec 2007 09:12:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Could this also be related to GRAILS-1869 (strange log4j additivity DSL behaviour in Config.groovy) ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14463841" author="brassrat" created="Wed, 5 Dec 2007 10:45:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;absolutely&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ConfigSlurper does not appear to map nested &apos;closures&apos; correctly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14463870" author="graemerocher" created="Thu, 6 Dec 2007 06:03:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This seems to have been corrected by an earlier issue related to closures and the way they behaved in RC3. I believe the changeset is one of these ones:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.groovy.codehaus.org/changelog/groovy/trunk/groovy/groovy-core?cs=9628&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.groovy.codehaus.org/changelog/groovy/trunk/groovy/groovy-core?cs=9628&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.groovy.codehaus.org/changelog/groovy/trunk/groovy/groovy-core?cs=9482&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.groovy.codehaus.org/changelog/groovy/trunk/groovy/groovy-core?cs=9482&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;None the less I&apos;ve included a test for this behaviour in &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.groovy.codehaus.org/browse/groovy/trunk/groovy/groovy-core/src/test/groovy/util/ConfigSlurperTest.groovy?r=HEAD&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.groovy.codehaus.org/browse/groovy/trunk/groovy/groovy-core/src/test/groovy/util/ConfigSlurperTest.groovy?r=HEAD&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So it doesn&apos;t happen again&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
